## Rule 5: Property vs Attribute Testing

Stencil maps `@Prop()` to both HTML attributes and JS properties. Some props only work as properties (complex types like objects/arrays).

### Attribute Props (strings, booleans, numbers)

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Verify attribute props', async () => {
    const component = canvasElement.querySelector('modus-wc-button');
    await expect(component).toHaveAttribute('color', 'primary');
    await expect(component).toHaveAttribute('variant', 'filled');
  });
}
```

### Property Props (objects, arrays)

```typescript
// Set via lit .property syntax
export const WithData: Story = {
  render: () => html`
    <modus-wc-table .data=${[{ id: 1, name: 'Row 1' }]}></modus-wc-table>
  `,
  play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
    const canvas = within(canvasElement);

    await step('Verify data rendered', async () => {
      const row = await canvas.findByText('Row 1');
      await expect(row).toBeInTheDocument();
    });
  },
};
```

